question: Ashley has 11 jars of chocolate chips in her storage room. Each jar of chocolate chips can decorate 12 brownies. Ashley wants to bake enough brownies to use up all of her chocolate chips. If each tray holds 12 brownies, how many trays worth of brownies should she bake?
answer:
She has enough chocolate chips for 11 * 12 = <<11*12=132>>132 brownies.
She needs 132 / 12 = <<132/12=11>>11 trays to bake all of the brownies.
#### 11
